Project 02: External Blinking LED

Now that I understand the basics of the Arduino, I took the next step: building a physical circuit! For this project, I learned how to use a breadboard, connect jumper wires, and use a resistor to safely power an external LED without burning it out.

🛠 Hardware Used

Microcontroller: Elegoo Uno R3

Breadboard: Half-size solderless breadboard

Components: * 1x External LED (Red)

1x 220-ohm Resistor (to protect the LED)

Jumper wires

Pin Connection: Digital Pin 9

